    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Driver-grade project with strong bones and plenty of usable life left. Starts, runs, and moves out well, with a willing powertrain, solid oil pressure behavior, and a chassis that still feels planted. Not a cosmetic queen and it shows its age, but it\u2019s the kind of car you can drive, improve, and enjoy while sorting the details. Great candidate for a budget commuter, weekend tinker build, or parts-friendly platform. Sold as-is, priced for someone who knows what they\u2019re looking at and wants a capable car without spending big money.",
      "price": 6900.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 17
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Cheap ride. Rough shape, but it runs and gets the job done. Priced to move fast.",
      "price": 3900.0,
      "reputation": 1.0,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 17
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_4_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_4",
      "description": "This car has the kind of honest, road-worn character that turns heads for all the right reasons\u2014a machine with stories in its metal and plenty of life left for someone who appreciates substance over showroom shine. It\u2019s an ideal fit for a hands-on owner, a first project, or anyone looking for inexpensive wheels with personality. There\u2019s a raw, usable appeal here: get in, make it your own, and enjoy a vehicle that offers freedom, function, and a chance to shape something memorable without a big upfront spend.",
      "price": 5900.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 17
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_5_listing_5",
